Constructor Detail

OptionsPane

public OptionsPane(java.lang.String key,
                   java.lang.String title,
                   ParameterPanelHandler parameterPanel,
                   java.awt.event.ActionListener displayActionListener)
            throws PluginException
Creates an options pane: plugin parameter panel with "Display", "OK", "Cancel" buttons. The "OK", "Cancel" buttons are handled internally, 'displayActionListener' handles the "Display" button.

Parameters:
key - is the plugin key
title - is the plugin title (usually menu string)
parameterPanel - is the plugin parameter panel
displayActionListener - is the event handler of the "Display" button with action command "plugin_"+key, no "Display" button is put if set to null

setDisplayButtonEnabled

public void setDisplayButtonEnabled(boolean enable)
Enables / disables "Display" button. Sets cursor accordingly: Cursor.WAIT_CURSOR for disabled state, Cursor.DEFAULT_CURSOR for enabled state.

Parameters:
enable - is true if to be enabled
